// Adversarial: QuickStop on the Breaker with a 3.0x deceleration multiplier under extreme
// chaos (0.8 action probability). Corridor layout with hard left/right walls means the
// breaker reaches edges frequently. The adversarial conditions: rapid direction reversals
// at wall edges, dash attempts mid-deceleration, and QuickStop multiplier stacking if
// reverse() is missed. If the breaker position is not clamped after a dash that overshoots,
// BreakerPositionClamped fires. If ActiveQuickStops accumulates without reversal,
// the breaker freezes in a degenerated state and BreakerInBounds may fire on the next
// dash. NoNaN covers f32 corruption in velocity/position under extreme deceleration.
// 5000 frames of high-chaos input maximises edge-case breaker state machine transitions.
(
    breaker: "Aegis",
    layout: "Corridor",
    input: Chaos((action_prob: 0.8)),
    max_frames: 5000,
    disallowed_failures: [BreakerInBounds, BreakerPositionClamped, NoNaN],
    allowed_failures: None,
    debug_setup: None,
    allow_early_end: false,
    seed: 8191,
    initial_effects: [
        On(target: Breaker, then: [
            When(trigger: Bumped, then: [
                Do(QuickStop(multiplier: 3.0)),
            ]),
        ]),
    ],
)
